This paper is about entity linking, which is a natural language processing task that involves linking named entities in text to their corresponding entries in a knowledge base. This task is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and databases (cs.DB). Given that the paper focuses on developing a multilingual entity linking approach and evaluating it on a wide range of languages, it is likely to be relevant to researchers working in any of these sub-fields.
